      "content": "fair enough. but if you look at the data, it seems like the people who fight against high-density zoning (like the \"NIMBYs\") are usually just trying to protect their own property values rather than actually caring about neighborhood character. do you think their opposition is based on legitimate urban planning concerns, or is it mostly just self-interest disguised as something else?",
